Memorial Lecture for Korean Victims of Great Kanto Quake Given
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- A memorial lecture for the Korean victims was given in Tokyo on August 9 in demand of the probe into the truth about the massacre of Koreans and apology and reinstatement of the victims, 85 years after this massacre during the great quake that hit Kanto, Japan in September 1923. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was sponsored by the "executive committee" grouping Japanese and south Korean figures and Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the lecture speakers underscored the need for Japan to clarify its state responsibility for the above-said mass killings of Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A statement issued at the lecture urged the Japanese government to deeply reflect on the fact that it has concealed the truth about the above-said massacre, apologize for it and make positive efforts to reinstate the victims.

